<ref>{{cite book | last =Chametzky | first =Jules | last2 =Felstiner| first2 =John| last3 =Flanzbaum | first3 =Hilene | last4 = Hellerstein| first4 =Kathryn| authorlink = | title =Jewish American Literature: A Norton Anthology| publisher = [[W.W. Norton & Company]]| series = | volume = | edition = | date =2001 | location = | pages =137 | language = | url =https://books.google.com/books/about/Jewish_American_Literature.html?id=DwQlVoyHac8C | doi = | id = | isbn =9780393048094 | quote=}}</ref>\n* [[Norman Finkelstein]], poet and literary critic<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tabletmag.com/arts-and-culture/books/21429/scribes-and-scribblers/|title=Scribes and Scribblers - Tablet Magazine|website=www.tabletmag.com}}</ref>\n* [[Allen Ginsberg]], beat poet<ref>{{cite journal |last=Pacernick |first=Gary |year=1997 |title=Allen Ginsberg: An Interview |journal=American Poetry Review |volume=26 |issue=4 |pages=23\u201327 |jstor=27782470}}</ref>\n* [[Jacob Glatstein]], poet<ref>{{cite book | last =Chametzky | first =Jules | last2 =Felstiner| first2 =John| last3 =Flanzbaum | first3 =Hilene | last4 = Hellerstein| first4 =Kathryn| authorlink = | title =Jewish American Literature: A Norton Anthology| publisher = [[W.W. Norton & Company]]| series = | volume = | edition = | date =2001 | location = | pages =370 | language = | url =https://books.google.com/books/about/Jewish_American_Literature.html?id=DwQlVoyHac8C | doi = | id = | isbn =9780393048094 | quote=}}</ref>\n* [[Moyshe-Leyb Halpern]], poet<ref>{{cite book | last =Chametzky | first =Jules | last2 =Felstiner| first2 =John| last3 =Flanzbaum | first3 =Hilene | last4 = Hellerstein| first4 =Kathryn| authorlink = | title =Jewish American Literature: A Norton Anthology| publisher = [[W.W. Norton & Company]]| series = | volume = | edition = | date =2001 | location = | pages =245 | language = | url =https://books.google.com/books/about/Jewish_American_Literature.html?id=DwQlVoyHac8C | doi = | id = | isbn =9780393048094 | quote=}}</ref>\n* [[Stanley Kunitz]], poet<ref>{{cite book | last =Chametzky | first =Jules | last2 =Felstiner| first2 =John| last3 =Flanzbaum | first3 =Hilene | last4 = Hellerstein| first4 =Kathryn| authorlink = | title =Jewish American Literature: A Norton Anthology| publisher = [[W.W. Norton & Company]]| series = | volume = | edition = | date =2001 | location = | pages =433 | language = | url =https://books.google.com/books/about/Jewish_American_Literature.html?id=DwQlVoyHac8C | doi = | id = | isbn =9780393048094 | quote=}}</ref>\n* [[D.L. Lang]], poet <ref name=\"langdl\">{{cite web|url=https://reformjudaism.org/blog/2018/09/17/turning-poem-yom-kippur|website=reformjudaism.org|title=Tupodtrning: A Poem for Yom Kippur|accessdate=15 October 2019}}</ref> \n* [[Emma Lazarus]], poet<ref>{{cite book |last=Young |first=Bette Roth |year=1997 |title=Emma Lazarus in Her World: Life and Letters |publisher=Jewish Publication Society |page=5 |isbn=9780827606180}}</ref>\n* [[Mani Leib]], poet<ref>{{cite book | last =Chametzky | first =Jules | last2 =Felstiner| first2 =John| last3 =Flanzbaum | first3 =Hilene | last4 = Hellerstein| first4 =Kathryn| authorlink = | title =Jewish American Literature: A Norton Anthology| publisher = [[W.W. Norton & Company]]| series = | volume = | edition = | date =2001 | location = | pages =217| language = | url =https://books.google.com/books/about/Jewish_American_Literature.html?id=DwQlVoyHac8C | doi = | id = | isbn =9780393048094 | quote=}}</ref>\n* [[Jeffrey Levine (poet)|Jeffrey Levine]], poet<ref>http://www.harvardreview.org/?q=authors/jeffrey-levine</ref>\n* [[Anna Margolin]], poet<ref>{{cite book | last =Chametzky | first =Jules | last2 =Felstiner| first2 =John| last3 =Flanzbaum | first3 =Hilene | last4 = Hellerstein| first4 =Kathryn| authorlink = | title =Jewish American Literature: A Norton Anthology| publisher = [[W.W. Norton & Company]]| series = | volume = | edition = | date =2001 | location = | pages =264 | language = | url =https://books.google.